**Steps to Reproduce**:

Using the following repro, getting the speculative semantic model for the method body fails no matter where I put the "position":

```csharp
using Microsoft.CodeAnalysis;
using Microsoft.CodeAnalysis.CSharp;
using Microsoft.CodeAnalysis.CSharp.Syntax;
using Microsoft.CodeAnalysis.Testing;
using System.Collections.Immutable;
using System.Runtime.InteropServices;

string source = @"
partial class Foo
{
    public partial void Method(int i)$$;
}"; 

/* This also fails if do any of the following:
public partial void $$Method(int i);
public partial void Method($$int i);
public partial void Method(int$$ i);
public partial void Method(int $$i);
public partial void Method(int i$$);
public partial void Method(int i);$$

*/

TestFileMarkupParser.GetPosition(source, out var parsed, out int position);

SyntaxTree tree = CSharpSyntaxTree.ParseText(parsed);
Compilation comp = CSharpCompilation.Create("Test", syntaxTrees: ImmutableArray.Create(tree));

SemanticModel model = comp.GetSemanticModel(tree);

string newMethodImpl = @"
public partial void Method(int i)
{
    int j = i;
    return j;
}";

bool success = model.TryGetSpeculativeSemanticModelForMethodBody(position, (MethodDeclarationSyntax)SyntaxFactory.ParseMemberDeclaration(newMethodImpl)!, out SemanticModel? speculativeModel);
if (success)
{
    Console.WriteLine("Created model");
}
else
{
    Console.WriteLine("Failure");
}
```

**Expected Behavior**:

Prints "Created model".

**Actual Behavior**:

Prints "Failure"

